amily%20member%20told%20us%20about%20a%20little%20girl%20who%20needed%20a%20home.%20At%20first%2C%20we%20thought%20the%20idea%20was%20crazy%2C%20having%20just%20been%20married%20weeks%20before%2C%20but%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmultigenerational-family-vacation-tips-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efamily%20member%3C%2Fa%3E%20assured%20us%20the%20process%20would%20be%20long%20and%20we%20could%20finish%20college%20before%20she%20would%20be%20placed.%20We%20thought%20and%20prayed%20about%20it%2C%20ultimately%20deciding%20it%20was%20something%20we%20could%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20some%20external%20factors%20sped%20up%20the%20process%2C%20and%20there%20was%20a%20need%20for%20her%20to%20come%20into%20our%20home%20much%20sooner%2C%20so%2C%20after%20a%20couple%20of%20months%20from%20saying%20%26quot%3Byes%2C%26quot%3B%20we%20brought%20home%20our%20daughter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20days%2C%20we%20moved%20off%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollege-admissions-tip-visit-cafeteria-on-campus-meet-students-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecollege%20campus%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20into%20a%20two-bedroom%20apartment.%20We%20shifted%20schedules%2C%20bought%20new%20furniture%2C%20and%20told%20our%20parents%20(not%20in%20that%20order!).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20lives%20were%20changed%20in%20ways%20we%20had%20never%20expected%2C%20and%20although%20it%20was%20stressful%20at%20times%2C%20I%20wouldn't%20change%20how%20we%20learned%20and%20grew%20as%20a%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f32c243f-d318-49ab-9088-3122edf1d482%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EOur%20peer%20group%20changed%20in%20an%20instant%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20greatest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmother-surprised-she-enjoying-son-progression-from-child-to-teen-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurprises%20of%20parenthood%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20a%20young%20age%20was%20losing%20one%20peer%20group%20and%20developing%20a%20new%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20we%20were%20a%20young%20couple%20with%20no%20kids%2C%20so%20we%20tried%20to%20cultivate%20relationships%20with%20couples%20in%20the%20same%20category%20for%20the%20first%20six%20months%20of%20our%20marriage.%20We%20even%20had%20a%20couple%20over%20the%20same%20night%20we%20found%20out%20we%20were%20becoming%20parents%2C%20and%2C%20to%20our%20surprise%2C%20they%20never%20came%20back%20around%20after%20our%20family%20grew.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20our%20college%20peer%20group%20gave%20way%20to%20deeper%20friendships%20with%20many%20of%20our%20professors%20who%20were%20also%20growing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpros-cons-big-family-independent-kids-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyoung%20families%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Talk%20about%20a%20vibe%20shift.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20still%20often%20find%20it%20strange%20that%20the%20same%20holds%20true%20today.%20Many%20of%20our%20closest%20friendships%20are%20with%20peers%20five%20to%2010%20years%20older%20than%20us%20because%20we%20have%20kids%20of%20similar%20ages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20realized%20our%20kid%20would%20determine%20many%20things%20for%20us%20and%20would%20shape%20how%20we%20relate%20to%20our%20peers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f249dabf-1e96-413a-9f65-f6f32c97e916%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20experienced%20layers%20of%20challenges%2C%20quickly%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20endured%20some%20significant%20stress%20points%20in%20the%20early%20days%2C%20and%20the%20learning%20curve%20to%20parenting%20a%203-year-old%20was%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20we%20were%20still%20aiming%20to%20finish%20university%20within%20four%20years%20and%20earn%20enough%20to%20sustain%20ourselves%20while%20finalizing%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadoption-is-my-first-choice-for-motherhood-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadoption%20process%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVery%20simply%2C%20we%20were%20in%20over%20our%20heads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20took%20things%20day%20by%20day%2C%20but%20our%20new%20normal%20was%20hard%20to%20navigate.%20We%20decided%20to%20put%20our%20daughter%20into%20two%20twice-a-week%20preschools%20to%20accommodate%20our%20schedules.%20This%20wasn't%20an%20easy%20choice%20for%20us%20because%20we%20also%20knew%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-change-your-attachment-style-from-avoidant-to-secure-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebonding%20and%20attachment%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20early%20days%20of%20adoption%20are%20critical%2C%20but%20our%20packed%20schedules%20made%20preschool%20a%20much-needed%20option.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDecisions%20like%20these%20happened%20on%20almost%20a%20daily%20basis%2C%20and%20the%20fear%20of%20not%20knowing%20what%20was%20right%20(and%20not%20just%20easy)%20was%20sometimes%20overwhelming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220e6766c5-0f68-4549-8606-f9150a8ef50e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EOur%20community%20surrounded%20us%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20challenges%20would%20likely%20have%20completely%20destabilized%20us%2C%20but%20our%20community%20rallied%20around%20us%20in%20a%20way%20we%20never%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20family%20doctor%2C%20lawyer%2C%20therapist%2C%20babysitters%2C%20and%20friends%20were%20all%20embedded%20in%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmother-spent-thousands-to-reveal-daughters-college-commitment-bed-party-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecollege%20community%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20was%20already%20happy%20with%20the%20education%20I%20was%20getting%20at%20the%20school%2C%20but%20the%20type%20of%20community%20support%20we%20received%20is%20what%20solidifies%20my%20fond%20memories%20of%20our%20days%20in%20university.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20we%20had%20tough%20decisions%20as%20a%20family%2C%20we%20had%20support%20and%20mentorship%20that%20helped%20us%20navigate%20each%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20I%20had%20to%20advise%20anyone%20in%20a%20similar%20situation%2C%20I%20would%20tell%20them%20that%20connecting%20deeply%20with%20a%20community%20was%20the%20key%20to%20our%20ability%20to%20navigate%20our%20early%20days%20as%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b10be1c3-607b-4e69-babf-a055a26a0640%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20made%20us%20into%20who%20we%20are%20today%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20early%20days%20as%20parents%20weren't%20easy%2C%20and%20we%20made%20a%20lot%20of%20rookie%20mistakes.%20A%20lot%20of%20the%20time%2C%20we%20felt%20like%20kids%20raising%20a%20kid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%2C%20those%20tough%20early%20days%20produced%20a%20foundation%20that%20has%20carried%20us%20through.%20We%20are%20more%20flexible%2C%20resourceful%2C%20and%20willing%20than%20we%20would%20have%20been%20otherwise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20my%20partner%20and%20I%20have%20four%20kids%20and%20are%20very%20grateful%20for%20the%20unique%20beginning%20of%20our%20lives%20as%20parents.%20We%20now%20allow%20the%20lessons%20learned%20to%20inform%20what%20we%20do%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollege-students-adopted-first-child-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1746367622000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6813ddf03fe8d3928364b246%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcollege-students-adopted-first-child-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20adoption%20process%20happened%20much%20faster%20than%20we%20expected%2C%20so%20my%20wife%20and%20I%20became%20parents%20in%20college.%20It%20completely%20changed%20our%20social%20circle.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(%20Johnathan%20Shuman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%