2https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgave-number-postman-crush-married-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nearly%20two-thirds%20of%20Americans%20fear%20going%20broke%20more%20than%20death.%20Here's%20how%20to%20avoid%203%20retirement-saving%20mistakes.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227708%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20woman%20with%20her%20head%20in%20her%20hands%20sitting%20at%20a%20desk%20looking%20frustrated%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679bb488eb4be2fff9a2f099%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225146%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%20(not%20pictured)%20felt%20lost%20when%20she%20achieved%20her%20career%20goals.%3Cp%3Ejacoblund%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E64%25%20of%20Americans%20fear%20running%20out%20of%20money%20more%20than%20death%2C%20per%20Allianz%20Life%20study.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMarket%20volatility%20and%20inflation%20in%202025%20heighten%20financial%20insecurity%20among%20Americans.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EExperts%20advise%20having%20a%20written%20retirement%20plan%20and%20understanding%20Social%20Security%20rules.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20two-thirds%20of%20Americans%2C%2064%25%2C%20worry%20more%20about%20running%20out%20of%20money%20than%20they%20do%20about%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20according%20to%20Allianz%20Life's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.allianzlife.com%2Fabout%2Fnewsroom%2F2025-Press-Releases%2FAmericans-Are-More-Worried-About-Running-Out-of-Money-Than-Death%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2025%20Annual%20Retirement%20Study%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20surveyed%201%2C000%20individuals%20age%2025%2B%20living%20in%20the%20contiguous%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20been%20getting%20this%20response%20for%20quite%20a%20while%20%E2%80%94%20that%20people%20are%20more%20afraid%20of%20running%20out%20of%20money%20than%20death%20%E2%80%94%20but%2064%20%25%20is%20the%20highest%20percentage%20that%20I%20recall%2C%26quot%3B%20Kelly%20LaVigne%2C%20the%20vice%20president%20of%20consumer%20insights%20at%20Allianz%20Life%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20attributes%20the%20higher%20percentage%20to%20market%20volatility%20and%20general%20uncertainty%20in%202025.%20The%20study%20also%20found%20that%20more%20than%20half%20of%20Americans%20say%20inflation%20contributes%20to%20their%20fear%20of%20running%20out%20of%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fear%20is%20justifiable%3A%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcrr.bc.edu%2Fthe-national-retirement-risk-index-version-2-0%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Retirement%20Risk%20Index%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20about%20half%20of%20households%20%26quot%3Bwill%20not%20be%20able%20to%20maintain%20their%26quot%3B%20preretirement%20living%20standard%2C%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-saving-why-half-retirees-could-run-out-of-money-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20Morningstar%20simulated%20model%3C%2Fa%3E%20shows%20that%20about%2045%25%20of%20Americans%20who%20leave%20the%20workforce%20at%2065%20risk%20running%20out%20of%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20among%20the%20majority%20and%20worry%20you're%20not%20saving%20enough%20for%20your%20future%2C%20start%20by%20addressing%20costly%20retirement%20mistakes%20to%20get%20back%20on%20track.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Make%20a%20plan%20and%20write%20it%20down.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ELaVigne%20says%20that%20one%20of%20the%20most%20common%20retirement%20mistakes%20is%20not%20having%20a%20written%20plan%20that%20accounts%20for%20various%20scenarios%2C%20including%20market%20corrections.%20A%20plan%20will%20not%20only%20help%20you%20achieve%20your%20retirement%20goals%2C%20but%20it%20will%20also%20provide%20a%20sense%20of%20security%20during%20times%20of%20uncertainty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20going%20to%20be%20some%20bumps%20in%20the%20road%2C%20like%20the%20volatility%20that%20we're%20going%20through%20right%20now%2C%20but%20if%20you%20have%20a%20good%20plan%20with%20contingencies%20in%20place%2C%20it%20will%20help%20you%20to%20get%20through%20the%20fear%20of%20running%20out%20of%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20LaVigne.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStart%20with%20figuring%20out%20your%20%26quot%3Bnumber%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20%E2%80%94%20the%20amount%20of%20money%20you%20want%20to%20save%20before%20leaving%20the%20workforce.%20Don't%20just%20consider%20your%20essential%20costs%3B%20think%20about%20what%20lifestyle%20you%20want%20in%20retirement%20and%20how%20you%20want%20to%20spend%20your%20days.%20If%20you%20want%20to%20travel%2C%20for%20example%2C%20factor%20in%20those%20additional%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWriting%20up%20a%20plan%20is%20a%20simple%20first%20step%20to%20take%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20necessarily%20easy%2C%20said%20LaVigne%3A%20%26quot%3BIt%20does%20require%20some%20dedication.%20It%20requires%20you%20to%20be%20honest.%20It%20requires%20some%20discipline%20to%20say%2C%20'OK%2C%20what%20am%20I%20really%20spending%20my%20money%20on%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Understand%20Social%20Security.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EYou%20can%20start%20receiving%20Social%20Security%20as%20early%20as%20age%2062%2C%20but%20that%20doesn't%20necessarily%20mean%20you%20should.%20In%20fact%2C%20many%20Americans%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-social-security-regrets-401k-divorce-moving-financial-mistakes-aarp-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eregret%20taking%20it%20prematurely%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDon't%20just%20take%20Social%20Security%20because%20you%20turned%2062%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20LaVigne.%20%26quot%3BIt%20could%20be%20the%20right%20thing%20for%20you%20%E2%80%94%20I'm%20not%20an%20advocate%20for%20everybody%20waiting%20until%20age%2070%20%E2%80%94%20but%20knowing%20the%20rules%20around%20how%20Social%20Security%20works%20is%20a%20really%2C%20really%20important%20part.%20It's%20not%20going%20to%20be%20your%20entire%20retirement%20income%2C%20but%20for%20the%20average%20American%2C%20it%20is%20about%2040%25%20of%20their%20retirement%20income.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20important%20to%20understand%20the%20rules%20%E2%80%94%20for%20example%2C%20delaying%20claiming%20Social%20Security%20until%20after%20your%20full%20retirement%20age%20results%20in%20bigger%20monthly%20checks%20%E2%80%94%20in%20order%20to%20properly%20strategize%20and%20maximize%20this%20benefit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Don't%20panic.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIt's%20easier%20said%20than%20done%2C%20especially%20amid%20market%20volatility%20that's%20outside%20your%20control%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Boverall%2C%20the%20best%20thing%20to%20do%20is%20not%20panic%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20LaVigne.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStay%20the%20course%2C%20stick%20to%20your%20plan%2C%20and%20don't%20let%20other%20people's%20decisions%20impact%20yours%3A%20%26quot%3BDon't%20be%20the%20one%20that%20says%2C%20'Oh%2C%20everybody's%20pulling%20their%20money%20out.%20I'm%20going%20to%20pull%20my%20money%20out.'%20And%20then%20six%20months%20or%20two%20years%20later%2C%20'Oh%2C%20I%20hear%20people%20are%20putting%20their%20money%20in.%20The%20market%20is%20rallying.'%20By%20the%20time%20the%20market's%20rallying%2C%20you've%20already%20missed%20some%20of%20the%20best%20days%20in%20the%20market.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETime%20in%20the%20market%20beats%20timing%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20hardest%20part%20about%20investing%20in%20the%20market%20over%20the%20long-term%20and%20for%20retirement%20is%20being%20able%20to%20sustain%20your%20position%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20But%20it's%20essential%2C%20even%20amid%20market%20dips%20and%20dives%2C%20which%20are%20uncomfortable%20but%20%26quot%3Bsometimes%20a%20natural%20part%20of%20the%20investment%20cycle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D